Not at all; it’s thoughtful, and an example of the rapidly eroding fine manners for which this country was once known. But it’s a question of courtesy, not necessity. You should offer a pregnant woman a seat just as you would offer a seat to a person older than you, or a person who looks a bit more tired than you do.
